            <title>[OPENJPA-1203] JPA2 - createEMF should return null for unhandled PUs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1203</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;JPA2 spec section 9.2 states - &quot;If a provider does not qualify as the provider for the named persistence unit, it must return null when createEntityManagerFactory is invoked on it.&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
But OpenJPA is throwing exceptions for all failure cases...&lt;br/&gt;
For now, we&apos;ll keep the 1.x behavior, but may need to revisit this when we start running the JPA2 TCK.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
